We recommended that Management:

Direct the OIC-CPDO to enhance the monitoring of the implementation of the projects in coordination with the implementing office, the CEO, to determine the cause/s for the delayed and non-implementation of the projects.  They should regularly submit status reports to the City Mayor for her information so that appropriate measures can be instituted to obtain the desired results;

Instruct the OIC-City Engineer (CE) to validate actual percentage of completion of the projects which should have been completed in December, 2016;

Direct the OIC-CE to coordinate with the OIC-CPDO and OIC-City Budget Officer to ensure that the actual amount budgeted is programmed for the projects; and

Direct the City Accountant to impose liquidated damages for projects which were completed beyond the contract period, if any.

